"flocculator, there are still velocity gradients which mean that there could be "
"some additional flocculation happening in the sedimentation tank. In the "
"flocculator, the main mechanism that led to flocculation was the deformation "
"of fluid which caused particles to collide. In the sedimentation tank, the "
"main mechanism that can lead to flocculation is velocity gradients. "
"Flocculation is provided by an opportunity for collision by differences in "
"relative velocities of particles. Big particles in the sedimentation tank "
"settle out but are still in suspension, and small particles continue to move "
"up through the large particles. There is relative velocity between particles "
"based on their terminal velocities."
msgstr ""
